---
title: Hoisin Fish Tacos with Wedges and Lime Mayo
description: Perfect for entertaining, or treating yourself midweek, our deliciously fresh hoisin fish tacos are a total crowd-pleaser. We’ve used coley in this dish for its flaky texture and marinated it in a deliciously sweet and sticky hoisin sauce that works really well with the zesty mayo dressing and crunchy veg. After marinating, the coley only needs to cook in a glug of olive oil a few minutes per side in a frying pan. Let the fish rest a few minutes before sprinkling over the sesame seeds and using a fork to flake it into pieces. Serve everything up in the middle of your table and get everyone to build their own tacos.
